  "texts": [
    "The extreme in this regard is attained on the binary Trust question by GPT-4, a model that seems to have learned never to trust people.",
    "More generally, out of the 13 models we tested, only the 4 instruct models (among which GPT-4) were consistent with Bisbee et al. (2024) 's result of low entropy, where each prompt leads to answers very concentrated on a single level.",
    "Foundational models showed more balanced answer distributions, where several answer levels have equivalent probabilities.",
    "GPT 3.5, for instance, is closer to Russia on the politics question, and Llama-3-8B mostly echoes the answers of Mexicans to the happiness question (see Appendix E.4).",
    "Furthermore, during and after training, LLMs are selected according to their performance on a series of natural language and reasoning tasks, much less on factual knowledge capabilities."
  ],
